Chinese troops under the Xinjiang Military Command recently conducted a live-fire drill for a new-type truck-mounted artillery unit in high altitude areas. After receiving orders from commanders, the soldiers immediately spread out according to their formation and set the truck-mounted artillery accordingly. During the drill, a variety of firing methods including single and simultaneous shooting, and shooting at the same pace were carried out, which comprehensively tested the capabilities of the truck-mounted artillery in high altitude areas.